imdb.title: Monster Hunter Stories: Ride On
imdb.plot: In a world where people and monsters are at odds, some learn to coexist. Known as Riders, they awaken the powers of monsters and live alongside them in secrecy. Now, one young boy journeys to find his own companion and become the ...

episodes.title: The Power of Bonds
episodes.plot: Aspiring young Rider Lute and friends go in search of a Monstie Egg on the eve of the Kinship Rite--a search that takes them into dangerous territory.

episodes.title: A Monstie is Born
episodes.plot: It's Kinship Rite time! Lilia and Cheval are uncertain about their futures, while an unexpected attack on Hakum Village sends its Riders scrambling.

episodes.title: Absolue Power
episodes.plot: A Hunter is headed for secretive Hakum Village. He's sure to have his own way of dealing with all these monsters showing up where they don't belong...

episodes.title: The Kinship Rite
episodes.plot: Chief Omna sends the apprentice Riders off in search of the Waterfall of Trials. A visitor to Hakum Village gives Lilia inspiration for her future.

episodes.title: Off to the Monstie Races
episodes.plot: Hakum Village revives the beloved Monstie Races for their four newest Riders, but Lute could still use a lot more practice piloting his powerful pal.

episodes.title: Quest for the Golden Egg
episodes.plot: Lute and friends dream about what they'd buy with the proceeds from a rare and valuable golden Gargwa egg, and Cheval decides to try hunting one down.

episodes.title: Like Mom Used to Make
episodes.plot: The mischievous twins Den-Den and Lin-Lin are stirring up trouble in Hakum Village--and run into trouble of their own in the forboding woods at night.

episodes.title: Navirou in Love
episodes.plot: Ms. Pink the traveling merchant stops by the village, and Navirou falls hard for her Felyne assistant Mocha. How far will he go in the name of love?

episodes.title: DSZ (Dan and Silva's Zeal)
episodes.plot: Dan has doubts about whether he should be leading the Riders in training, and remembers his old friend Silva, who was once a shoo-in to be the leader.

episodes.title: Portent of Disaster
episodes.plot: In the latest ill omen, the village's beneficial wind turns violent. Hyoro struggles to live up to the expectations of his demanding brother Genie.

episodes.title: Before the Storm
episodes.plot: Lilia leads her friends into the woods to investigate the evil changes taking place. There they learn about a legendary Rider--and about Lute's folks.

episodes.title: Invasion of the Nargacuga
episodes.plot: A Blight-mad Nargacuga attacks the village, leaving a trail of blind destruction in its wake as Riders young and old do all they can to drive it away.

episodes.title: A Rathian is Born
episodes.plot: There's no time to clean up after the Nargacuga when it could attack the village again at any moment. Cheval swears revenge and takes a new Monstie.

episodes.title: Face the Black Blight
episodes.plot: The apprentice Riders go off on their own to face the Blighted Nargacuga, but it's going to be tough with Lute's Monstie still recovering back home...

episodes.title: The Journey Begins
episodes.plot: The time has come for the young Riders to venture forth beyond Hakum Village, accompanied by excitement, responsibility, and not a little trepidation.

episodes.title: Avinia's Secret
episodes.plot: Having started their journey outside the village, Lute and Navirou get separated from the others, and find a girl who is hurt and in need of help.

episodes.title: Meet the Riddlemaster
episodes.plot: Lute, Navirou, and Avinia encounter an enigmatic, riddle-loving innkeeper who stands between them and the help Avinia needs for her beloved Monstie.

episodes.title: Welcome to Gildegaran
episodes.plot: Lute and friends are dazzled by the big city, but they soon get down to business: finding the Scriveners and a way to keep the Black Blight in check.

episodes.title: Nerscylla Blitz
episodes.plot: It's questing time in the Hunter city of Gildegaran! A task that looks like a piece of cake winds up being more than Lute and Navirou bargained for.

episodes.title: The Legend of Pawpad Place
episodes.plot: Lute and Lilia stumble across a Felyne village while searching for a Kinship Ore. Navirou is confronted by a strange Felyne who insists they're pals.

episodes.title: Barroth, Landslide Wyvern
episodes.plot: Lilia brings the young Riders a request from the Scriveners that sends them through a vast desert in search of a solution to the Black Blight problem.

episodes.title: Desert Mayday
episodes.plot: The group meets with Hunter opposition in the Oasum refugee camp. A desert battle with a Blighted monster gets an unexpected--and unwelcome--assist.

episodes.title: The Horned Wyvern's Lament
episodes.plot: Dan and the other senior Riders meet up with Lute's party in the desert, where Chief Nolma shares some info that changes the course of their quest.

episodes.title: Sky Wyvern, Land Wyvern
episodes.plot: The rift deepens between fellow Riders Lute and Cheval as their attitudes toward rogue monsters drift further apart. Lute reunites with an old friend.

episodes.title: Diabolical Diablos, Horned Wyvern
episodes.plot: After proving their mettle against the Blighted Diablos near the ruins of Reverto's hometown, the Riders reach an understanding about the road ahead.

episodes.title: The Mysterious White Dragon
episodes.plot: Lute wants the same Monstie as the legendary hero Redan--and Debli's teacher seems to know where to find precisely the Monster Egg he's looking for.

episodes.title: Dovan Volcano Memories
episodes.plot: Why does Navirou's head hurt at the very mention of the Dovan Volcano? Lute runs into a couple of troublemakers en route to the next Kinship Ore.

episodes.title: Onward, Numbers
episodes.plot: Discarded like so much trash, Navirou happens to reunite with some old friends. If only he could remember them--or the grand plans they had to escape.

episodes.title: The Dragon in the Sea of Fire
episodes.plot: Lute and the Numbers face off against Dr. Manelger in his subterranean lab, where the mad scientist has an unpleasant mechanized surprise for them.

episodes.title: Parting Ways
episodes.plot: Bent on destroying Blighted monsters, Cheval confronts Lute over his beloved Monstie Ratha, who may not even have the strength to defend himself.

episodes.title: Be the Forest, Be the Beast
episodes.plot: Lute and Reverto track a monster into a mine, despite rumors that it's haunted. Never mind what they find--what's more worrying is what finds THEM.

episodes.title: All Out, Airborne Assault
episodes.plot: There's a Blighted monster on Naubaka Island, but no one who sails there comes back. Lute and friends brave the waves with the unique Bandit Captain.

episodes.title: The Wolf Raven Strikes Back
episodes.plot: Lute and Avinia must defend lovely Koapni Village from the Blighted monster that's been terrorizing the island. Pansy has a big favor to ask Navirou.

episodes.title: Rainbow Beach Blockade
episodes.plot: Chief Mallerie's pickle weight has been stolen! Never fear: Detective Navirou is on the case. Meanwhile, Lute searches for Naubaka's Kinship Ore.

episodes.title: The White Dragon's Egg
episodes.plot: Lilia has a strong lead on the whereabouts of the legendary white dragon's egg that sends Lute and friends into the ruins of the hero Redan's village.

episodes.title: The Great Manelger Chase
episodes.plot: Lute follows a tip from the Scriveners to outside Albrachs Village as he tracks down Dr. Manelger, where he gets Hunter help--and a Hunter headache.

episodes.title: Trouble Returns to Hakum
episodes.plot: A second Kinship Ore in Hakum Village? Lute returns to his hometown just in time to deal with the devastating fallout of the mad Manelger's meddling.

episodes.title: The Little Bouquet
episodes.plot: Cheval is back in Hakum Village! He may be too late to slay the Blighted beast, but he sticks around to confront and challenge his former friend Lute.

episodes.title: Tested at the Tower of Illusion
episodes.plot: Chief Omna brings Lute to the Tower of Illusion, where he undergoes a tense trial meant to dispel the doubt from his mind and lead him to the truth.

episodes.title: Brachydios the Destroyer
episodes.plot: Lute accompanies Reverto on a quest to slay Brachydios the Destroyer, an ultra-powerful tempered monster and the expert Hunter's longtime rival.

episodes.title: The Nargacuga Returns
episodes.plot: Cheval takes on an unexpected--and hopefully more obedient--new Monstie before he and his team head to the desert to find a Black Diablos run amok.

episodes.title: Numbers, Assemble
episodes.plot: Lute and Navirou reunite with the Numbers as they search for another Kinship Ore on Mt. Rhyz, where some unexpected company puts their plans on hold.

episodes.title: Forest of Confusion
episodes.plot: Some familiar faces rejoin Lute on his journey into the Forest of Confusion, hot on the trail of the next Kinship Ore. But the Blight is spreading...

episodes.title: A Mystical Meeting with Kirin
episodes.plot: The team has a rare encounter with a mysterious Elder Dragon deep in the Forest of Confusion as they continue their search for the Kinship Ore.

episodes.title: The Deviljho of Mt Celion
episodes.plot: The final Kinship Ore waits amid freezing mountain ruins. Lute and Manelger are in hot pursuit, but Cheval's new Mechinship Stone changes everything.

episodes.title: The Legendary White Dragon is Born
episodes.plot: Cheval flexes his newfound muscle with his white dragon Monstie, but even he's not safe from the Black Blight. Lute seeks a chance to patch things up.

episodes.title: This is it: The Black Dread
episodes.plot: Lute and Cheval face the staggeringly powerful Black Dread, a monster capable of wiping entire villages off the map; Ratha has a fight of his own.

episodes.title: A Miracle in White
episodes.plot: Lute and Ratha's pitched battle with the formidable Black Dread rages on, but Lute's secret weapon--the power of Kinship--may finally turn the tide.
